ua.net.freecode.chart
Class Marker

java.lang.Object
  ua.net.freecode.chart.Marker
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Marker
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Determines the shape of markers to be placed for each x,y points in your data. There are ready markers: circle, square, ring, triangle upward, triangle downward, triangle leftward, triangle rightward, rectangle and even you can define your own markers using SVG path description (this is HTML5 standard) .

public Marker(int number,

You can create your own marker shapes.

Parameters:
number - the custom number of the shape: 0..239
svgPathD - the path description of the shape use the HTML5 standard for SVG PATH D parameter, for example: "m -3 0 l 6 3 l 0 -6 Z" Consider that at the beginning the cursor is set to the center of the marker.
